# Pull Request Management

Pull requests are the primary collaboration mechanism on GitHub. They propose changes from a head branch (or fork) into a base branch, enable code review, run CI checks via [[github/actions]], and provide a merge gate for protected branches.

## Sub-Skills

This skill is divided into focused sub-skills for specific PR operations:

- **[[github/pulls/create]]** — Create new pull requests from branches or forks
- **[[github/pulls/list]]** — List, search, and filter pull requests
- **[[github/pulls/review]]** — Request, submit, and manage code reviews
- **[[github/pulls/merge]]** — Merge, squash, or rebase pull requests

## Quick Reference

```bash
# Create a PR (gh CLI)
gh pr create --title "feat: add auth" --body "Adds JWT auth" --base main

# List open PRs
gh pr list --state open

# Review a PR
gh pr review 42 --approve --body "LGTM"

# Merge with squash
gh pr merge 42 --squash --delete-branch
```

```javascript
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";
const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

// Create PR
const { data: pr } = await octokit.pulls.create({
  owner: "my-org", repo: "my-project",
  title: "feat: add user authentication",
  body: "Adds JWT-based authentication.\n\nFixes #42",
  head: "feature/auth", base: "main",
});

// List PRs
const { data: prs } = await octokit.pulls.list({
  owner: "my-org", repo: "my-project",
  state: "open", sort: "created", direction: "desc",
});

// Submit review
await octokit.pulls.createReview({
  owner: "my-org", repo: "my-project",
  pull_number: 42, event: "APPROVE",
  body: "Code looks clean and tests are comprehensive.",
});

// Merge
await octokit.pulls.merge({
  owner: "my-org", repo: "my-project",
  pull_number: 42, merge_method: "squash",
});
```

## Merge Strategies

| Strategy | Command | Result |
|----------|---------|--------|
| Merge commit | `merge_method: "merge"` | Preserves all commits, adds merge commit |
| Squash | `merge_method: "squash"` | Combines into single commit |
| Rebase | `merge_method: "rebase"` | Replays commits on base, linear history |

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | Personal access token or installation token |
